		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
				<h1 class="firstHeading">WoW: Classes: Mage</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From GraffeWiki</h3>
			<div id="contentSub">
				<div id="mw-revision-info">Revision as of 16:56, 23 February 2007 by <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=User:Coren&amp;action=edit" class="new" title="User:Coren">Coren</a> (<a href="/wiki/index.php?title=User_talk:Coren&amp;action=edit" class="new" title="User talk:Coren">Talk</a> | <a href="/wiki/index.php/Special:Contributions/Coren" title="Special:Contributions/Coren">contribs</a>)</div>

				<div id="mw-revision-nav">(<a href="/wiki/index.php?title=WoW:_Classes:_Mage&amp;diff=prev&amp;oldid=1583" title="WoW: Classes: Mage">diff</a>) <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=WoW:_Classes:_Mage&amp;direction=prev&amp;oldid=1583" title="WoW: Classes: Mage">←Older revision</a> | Current revision (diff) | Newer revision→ (diff)</div>
			</div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Mages</b>
</p><p>Mages are the primary magical DPS class in <a href="/wiki/index.php/WoW" title="WoW">WoW</a> especially excelling at multitarget situations.  They may cast spells from and specialize in Arcane, Fire, or Frost magics. The differences in playstyle between the three schools of magic are varied and complex:
</p>
<a name="Arcane_Magics"></a><h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/index.php?title=WoW:_Classes:_Mage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Arcane Magics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline"> Arcane Magics </span></h2>
<p>Arcane magic tends to be a utility or novelty tree for most of a Mage's career. Many of a Mage's most used spells can be found in this school - Arcane Explosion, Polymorph, Conjure Food/Water, teleports and portals. However, until late in the game the school is decidedly subpar compared to the others in dealing damage. The advent of Arcane Blast at level 64 changes this, making Arcane into arguably the most effective damage-dealing tree to specialize in for group content.
</p><p>Arcane talents tend to focus around improving damage with all schools of magic, improving mana supply and efficiency, and a pair of high-powered cooldown talents that are ideal for PvP ganking (Presence of Mind and Arcane Power).
</p>
<a name="Fire_Magics"></a><h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/index.php?title=WoW:_Classes:_Mage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Fire Magics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline"> Fire Magics </span></h2>
<p>Fire mages specialize in maximizing damage per second (dps), focusing on doing as much damage as possible, as quickly as possible. It has neither the crowd control talents of the frost tree, nor the mana conservation and augmentation talents of the arcane tree, but generally does more raw damage than either alternative tree. This is not true at very high levels, due to some peculiarities involving a specific spell called [<a href="http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=30451" class="external text" title="http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=30451" rel="nofollow">Arcane Blast</a>]. It is unclear at this time if it is Blizzards intention for Arcane Blast to be outperforming the damage of the fire tree for both sustained and burst damage.
</p><p>Fire talents are very popular with leveling mages, as doing damage to mobs is the primary base mechanism to leveling, and fire tends to do this more effectively on a single target basis than other talent trees. Because they are able to burn single targets so fast, Fire Mages are able to level in nearly any area, and are not restricted as AE-based Frost mages are.
</p>
<a name="Frost_Magics"></a><h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/wiki/index.php?title=WoW:_Classes:_Mage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Frost Magics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline"> Frost Magics </span></h2>
<p>This class role is often sought after for their Crowd Control options. While Frost spells tend to be inferior to Fire spells and Arcane Blast in doing damage they are mana efficient and often have a snare component. Frost mages' ability to snare and freeze enemies allows them to kite mobs and keep them occupied in ways other mages cannot. Frost Mages gain the ability to cast <a href="/wiki/index.php/WoW:_Spells:_Mage:_Ice_Block" title="WoW: Spells: Mage: Ice Block">Ice Block</a>, which makes the mage immune to all attacks for 10 seconds and removes all debuffs; [<a href="http://www.wowhead.com/?search=ice+barrier" class="external text" title="http://www.wowhead.com/?search=ice+barrier" rel="nofollow">Ice Barrier</a>], which effectively gives them another 1000 hit points (and often even more in PvP situations); and [<a href="http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=12472" class="external text" title="http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=12472" rel="nofollow">Cold Snap</a>], which can instantly refresh any of their cooldowns.  Heavily spec'ed frost mages can also choose to <a href="/wiki/index.php/WoW:_Spells:_Mage:_Summon_Water_Elemental" title="WoW: Spells: Mage: Summon Water Elemental">Summon Water Elemental</a> to fight with them for a short amount of time. Frost is generally considered the most powerful defensive tree. 
</p><p>Frost is considered one of the best solo abilities for mages that prefer AE kiting.  This is accomplished by use of the Talents Improved Blizzard, and Permafrost.  The drawbacks of this leveling style are that it is highly location dependent, and can lead to frequent deaths from a run of 'bad luck' (such as getting multiple resists for Frost Nova).  In the Burning Crusade, many players have found that it is far more efficient to use single target spells for completing quests, and thus Fire is far more efficient at leveling than even AE kiting.
</p>
